Under the Watching Eye <br />
Orc Scimitar x 2 <br />
Thin & Stretched x 2  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Start out with 3 or 4 burdens and play your first site. Add a burden to play Aragorn from your deck and your fellowship is all there. Exert Sam when you get a little worried about the burdens you have. It pretty much just moves and fights on its own. You have plenty of things to help out all of your characters. Play what you can when you can.<br />
<br />
For the Shadow, there are a number of ways to play this. One thing you can do is slow your opponent by not playing any minions until their second site when the twilight pool is bigger. You might overwhelm him. If not, they might only move one site at a time.<br />
<br />
The heavy hitters of this deck are Aragorn and Arwen. Use them as you like. Also, every turn don&#39;t forget to use Aragorn&#39;s healing ability. If burdens are the trouble, Sam can practically heal one every turn for free. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
